cs.IT, cs.ITP, cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the broadcast channel. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses coding theory and the use of deterministic encoders, which could fall under cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). The paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for channel input distribution, which could fall under cs.MM (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the reliability of message identification, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
